        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Support z.ai BigModel team usage",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Extend shared token accounts with provider-specific usage scope and workspace/project metadata, matching the existing Claude per-account organization pattern while keeping the fields optional and provider-gated.\n- Add per-account z.ai Team mode in Settings/CLI: personal accounts explicitly clear team context; team accounts store BigModel organization and project IDs for that account.\n- Preserve the API-key path for z.ai team usage: quota requests use `type=2`, hourly model-usage requests use `type=3`, and both send `Bigmodel-Organization` / `Bigmodel-Project`.\n- Route selected team accounts to the BigModel team dashboard.\n\n## Why\nBigModel team Coding Plan usage can return `当前用户不存在coding plan` when queried through the personal quota path. The team quota and hourly usage paths still work with the z.ai API key, but they need the team selector query parameter and both BigModel organization/project headers. This avoids a cookie/session dependency while supporting common personal + team multi-account setups.\n\n## Test Plan\n- `./Scripts/lint.sh format`\n- `swift test --filter ZaiBigModelTeamScopeTests`\n- `swift test --filter ZaiTokenAccountEnvironmentTests`\n- `swift test --filter ZaiProviderTests`\n- `swift test --filter ZaiDashboardActionTests`\n- `swift test --filter ProvidersPaneCoverageTests`\n- `swift build --product CodexBarCLI`\n- `swift build --product CodexBar`\n- `make check`\n- `git diff --check`\n",
